---
title: Double Sauced Turkey Street Cart Bowls with Yellow Rice
description: Want your favorite street cart foods without having to track down your fave truck? Our chefs dreamed up just the thing: these turkey street cart-style rice bowls. Each bowl is packed with layers of flavor: buttery turmeric rice with crunchy almonds and scallions, shawarma spiced ground turkey, fresh diced tomato, and not one but TWO sauces. We’re talking classic white sauce and hot sauce. All of that’s served with warmed pita bread. Now all that’s left to do is perfect your dipping technique for the optimal saucy and flavor-packed bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/double-sauced-turkey-street-cart-bowls-4db11d08.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/double-sauced-turkey-street-cart-bowls-614210cbc5019e1d7106f890-e712247d.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Middle East
nutrition:
  calories: 1050 kcal
  fat: 58 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 98 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1480 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/double-sauced-turkey-street-cart-bowls-614210cbc5019e1d7106f890
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
---

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4 servings); stir to combine.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

Meanwhile, bring @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @ground turkey{10%oz}, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{3} and @water{1/4%cup}. Reduce heat to medium low and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @almonds{1/2%oz} and half the scallion greens. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Toast @whole wheat pitas{2}. Spread with softened @butter{}; cut each pita into four pieces.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with turkey and tomato in separate sections; sprinkle tomato with a pinch of @salt{}. Drizzle turkey with @hot sauce{2%tsp} to taste. Drizzle white sauce over bowls; garnish with remaining scallion greens. Serve with pitas and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> We like to scoop up some of the rice, turkey, tomato, and sauces with the pita and eat it all in one bite!